Added methods to send DB over I/O stream,Added two methods to Library class that can be used for sending the,library over a connection between devices. Each table in the library is,taken one by one and each of its rows' values along with column names,are put into a JSON object which is then sent over the provided,OutputStream. At the receiving end,the same JSON object is retrieved,from the InputStream and decoded back into a row and inserted into the,same table in the database. Still need to implement sending album art.,I've tried to write the methods as generalized as possible so that,changing columns or adding new tables in the future won't require,updating these methods.,Changes:,Table:,  -Added a constructor to get table name. This can be used by Library,  when accessing a table' name through abstract class 'Table' reference,  -added method to get a cursor of all columns and rows,  -added method to insert values into a new row in table,SongTable,AlbumTable,ArtistTable:,  -calls Table's new constructor,  -uses insertValues(),Library:,  -Forgot to set querySongs() ordering back to song title. (was set to,  album name for testing in previous commit),  -Added two methods for sending/receiving the entire library database,  over input/output streams as JSON objects

Reintroduced library with better implementation,removed splash gif,Decided to reintroduce the library database to try and see if it makes,transferring local database to remote devices easier. Content,provider is used only to obtain song,album and artist info and store,them into local tables in the library database. Required cursors are,queried from these tables. Allows querying between multiple tables which,the MediaStore could not do,and should hopefully make sending library,to other devices a simple process of sending columns of these tables.,This time,libraryDb uses transactions for loading the library making it,twice as fast as past Library DB implementation. Startup initialization,of database takes around 3 seconds on my device.,Removed album art path caching since its stored in the Library DB now.,Removed the splash screen Gif. It was funny while it lasted and slowed,down startup slightly.,Changes:,SplashActivity:,  -Removed splash animation. The joke's run on long enough. R.I.P.,  Eldorado breakdown,Library:,  -Changed functionality. Now an instantiable class used for editing or,  obtaining the library database.,  -Removed album art database,New Classes:,Table:,  -An abstract class for any table to be added to the database. Contains,  required methods used by Library so that future tables can be added,  without much changes required,SongTable,AlbumTable,ArtistTable:,  -Extensions of Table for holding Media,Album,Artist information from,  ContentResolver

ZooniverseClient,SubjectAdder: Disable Volley request caching.,Because it would not be useful to us and could theoretically,(if Volley doesn't check the timestamp),lead to us not doing a new network request for new items,,because the request always looks the same.
ItemsContentProvider: Use getExternalCacheDir() instead of getExternalFilesDir().,For the cached subject images. This seems like a more correct place,to put them.
Toolbar: Make the "Classify" action name appear dark on older devices.,By setting actionMenuTextColor.,This isn't necessary when running on Android 5.0 (API 21) but is,necessary on older devices.
Support API 11 (instead of 12) by using LruCache from AppCompat v4.
Use a style for the checkbox (ToggleButton).,However,I still don't see a way to keep the ripple effect,,because we cannot derive from the borderlessButtonStyle attr.
QuestionFragment: Define the ToggleButton state colors in a <selector> drawable.,Instead of in code.
Translations: Add an English string to fix the build.
QuestionFragment: Change the ToggleButton background when checked.,Because a ToggleButton with borderlessButtonStyle or otherwise,with a transparent background doesn't show any state otherwise.
QuestionFragment: inflate() the buttons from Layout XML.,This lets us specify the borderlessButtonStyle,instead of manually,setting the background.
SubjectAdder.cacheUriToFile(): After errors,unmark the download in progress.
SyncAdapter: requestMoreItemsAsync(): Do not stop trying after one failure.,onErrorResponse(): Unset mRequestMoreItemsTaskInProgress so we will try,next time.
Let errors stop Volley's RequestFuture.get().,Provide the RequestFuture as the errorListener too.,Otherwise it waits until the timeout,though the,onErrorResponse() is called while we are waiting.
LoginActivity: If the network fails (but exists) don't say the password is wrong.
Italian,Spanish translations: Add English strings to fix the build.
LoginActivity: Fix the crash due to a null ZooniverseClient.
strings.xml: About: Mention the use of the Volley library.

Use Volley for getting the JSON list of subjects and for getting the images.,The code is now a bit awkward,but it seems to have much better performance,,probably because it avoids doing too many simultaneous network requests.,Login and Upload are still using plain HttpURLConnection because they,are so simple.
ZoonAccountAuthenticatorActivity: Suppress the android-lint warning.,This doesn't need to be declared in the manifest because it is just a,base class.

LoginActivity: Show the Toolbar by using a copy of ActionBarActivity.,I don't like this at all,but there doesn't seem to be any way around it:,https://chris.banes.me/2014/10/17/appcompat-v21/#comment-1652981836

Action icons: Give the Invert icon rounded corners.,With a 2dp radius as specified here:,http://www.google.com/design/spec/style/icons.html#icons-system-icons,though the,"Each system icon size set requires a different round corner for optical consistency.",text there might be trying to say,in designese,that we need a custom SVG,for each icon size.,The PNGs were generated from the SVG with this:,http://romannurik.github.io/AndroidAssetStudio/icons-actionbar.html#source.type=image&source.space.trim=1&source.space.pad=0&name=ic_action_invert&theme=light&color=33b5e5%2C60

Action icons: Update the help icon to the latest from the Android Asset Studio.,This apparently the correct one to use with Material Design.,ic_action_help was generated from this:,http://romannurik.github.io/AndroidAssetStudio/icons-actionbar.html#source.type=clipart&source.space.trim=1&source.space.pad=0&source.clipart=res%2Fclipart%2Ficons%2Faction_help.svg&name=ic_action_action_help&theme=light&color=33b5e5%2C60,I can't tell if the other icons need to be updated too.
Material design: List: Specify elevation.,Though it's not clear how this should really be used,,and I doubt it will have a visible appearance on a dark theme.

Material design: Use the AppCompat textAppearance styles.,Because that is what this advises:,http://android-developers.blogspot.de/2014/10/implementing-material-design-in-your.html,Though I am not convinced that this is different than using the,normal attr styles such as "?android:attr/textAppearanceLarge".,Along the way,QuestinHelpFragment/fragment_question_help.xml got some textAppearance,styles where it had none.
Use the latest Android SDK build tools version.

Toolbar: Use a derived style to get a dark menu.,Instead of just using Theme.AppCompat.Light to get the dark title text,and overflow icon in the toolbar,use a special theme for the toolbar,that derives from Theme.AppCompat (with the dark menu) and change,textColorPrimary and textColorSecondary to get the dark title text,and overflow icon.,However,the menu colors are not quite right,because those two,values affect it too. But setting popupTheme on the <Toolbar>,lets us change the menu's theme back again,leaving our customization,only for the toolbar itself.,https://chris.banes.me/2014/10/17/appcompat-v21/
QuestionFragment: Make the answer buttons transparent.,This gets rid of the standard background drawable that draws margins that,we cannot otherwise avoid.

QuestionFragment: Reduce the minimum padding inside the answer buttons.,To avoid words being broken across lines on the "Is Anything Odd?",question with the Material (AppCompat) theme on,for instance,,a portrait Nexus 4.
Layout XML: Fix typos in the tools: attributes.,These were copy/paste errors.
Login: Move the toolbar up out of the LinearLayout that has padding.,So it is flush with the status bar and the sides,like the other,activities.
Material design: Use colors from the Material design palette.,Including specifying a colorPrimaryDark which changes the status bar,above the actionbar/toolbar,because that seems to be normal.
QuestionHelpFragment: Use a transition when opening the example image viewer.,By using the shared transitionName and ActivityCompat.startActivity().
BaseActivity: Move the transitionName into a constant in SubjectFragment.

SyncAdapter,SubjectAdder: Replace use of AsyncTask with Runnable and Thread.,Because older (API <15) versions of Android don't seem to like us using AsyncTask in,the SyncAdapter (which doesn't have the UI thread),giving us this ExceptionInInitializerError:,"Can't create handler inside thread that has not called Looper.prepare()".
SyncAdapter,SubjectAdder: AsyncTasks: Take parameters in the constructors.,This seems to be allowed. It is cleaner,requiring less runtime checks.,And it should make refactoring easier too.
HttpUtils.parseGetFileResponseContent(): Close the ParcelFileDescriptor.,To avoid leaking it. Discovered by StrictMode (see BaseActivity).
German translation: Add an (English) string to make the APK buildable.
Use the latest gradle plugin version.
gradle-wrapper.properties: Use HTTPS,which is the new default.

ZooniverseClient: Make Subject immutable by making internals private with no setters.,This makes the code rather verbose,but immutable classes are inherently,thread-safe. Even though we try not to use Subject across threads,it would be easy,to make that mistake,so this gives a little extra safety.
DecisionTree: Make some inner classes a bit more immutable.
ItemsContentProvider: Re-comment out onUpgrade(),left over after some debugging.
QuestionFragment: Restart: Do not change the itemID by getting "next" again.,Just wipe the classification in progress and clear the question ID,so we show the first question again.
DecisionTree: Make getFirstQuestion() private.,Because it is not used outside the class.

Plus a few fixes,# For android coders,Q: How do I copy and rename a file to a resource folder using android,studio gradle?,Oh,btw,did you know that this readme file is auto copied from the root,directory of the project folder,into this app's `/src/main/res/raw`,folder before being compiled?,It's quite a handy way to keep your readme file accessible in the,resource directory (e.g. so you can view the readme file from within,your app!),Here is how to do it. Copy the code below to your gradle buildfile in,/app/src/build.gradle . (You might need to adjust the "from" settings,,but should be self explanatory).,/*,* Based on,https://discuss.gradle.org/t/how-to-copy-and-rename-a-single-file/5956,* */,task copyreadme(type: Copy) {,from '../README.md',into 'src/main/res/raw',rename { String fileName ->,fileName.replace("README.md","readme.md"),},},tasks.copyreadme.execute(),Once you do that,everytime you build your file. It will auto copy the,readme file to the raw resource directory of your android project,folder. Let me know if it was handy!
